SOP: Creating a User with Account Expiry on Linux

Purpose

This Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) outlines the steps to create a
new user on a Linux system, set an account expiration date, and verify
the configuration.

Prerequisites

-   Root or sudo access to the Linux server.
-   SSH access to the target server.

Steps

1. SSH into the Server

Use SSH to connect to the target server:

    ssh banner@172.16.238.12

2. Switch to the Root User

    sudo su -

3. Create a New User

    useradd javed

4. Set Account Expiry Date

Set the account to expire on 2023‑12‑07:

    usermod -e 2023-12-07 javed

5. Verify the Account Settings

Check password and expiry details:

    chage -l javed

6. Expected Output Fields

-   Last password change
-   Password expiration
-   Password inactivity
-   Account expiration
-   Minimum days between password changes
-   Maximum days between password changes
-   Password expiry warning period

Notes

-   Expired accounts cannot log in after the set date.
-   Use chage -E -1 username to remove expiry if needed.
